The Ansar-Ud-Deen College, Isolo, Old Student Association (ADCIOSA) will be holding its annual Ramadan Lecture on Sunday. It is scheduled to take place at the Ansar-Ud-Deen College Hall, Isolo. According to the organisers, the topic is “Ramadan Kareem, To Whom It May Concern.”   Kano earmarks N550m for Sahur, Iftar     Fidau for Oniru’s mum holds today     Firm targets 2,000 jobs in finance sector   The guest speaker is former Chief Missioner of Nasrulahi-li-Fatih Society (NASFAT), Imam Abdullahi Akinbode, now founder, Jamaa’tu Ahli Llahi. Director-General of the Nigerian Nuclear Regulatory Authority (NNRA), Prof. Babatunde Elegba will be Guest of Honour while M.A.O Dabiri, an engineer will chair the event. The lecture, ADCIOSA said, would enliven members’ quest to maximize the benefit of Ramadan. Prayers, the alumni said, will be offered for the nation to surmount the security challenges.